This paper proposes a novel object proposal generation network that utilizes different resolutions of feature maps to detect objects of various sizes. This is a common problem in computer vision, particularly in object detection, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning techniques such as deconvolution and recursive training, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of anchor candidates and region proposals, which are common in robotics (cs.RO) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, and cs.RO, in that order.
